COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
State of Oklahoma
SPEAKER:
CHAIR:
I move to amend HB4225
Of the printed Bill
Page 2 Section Lines 20 1/2
Of the Engrossed Bill
"SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified in the
Oklahoma Statutes as Section 935.12 of Title 74, unless there is created a
duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
A. A plan participant may borrow from the participant's account
balance the lessor of:
1. Fifty percent (50%) of the participant's vested account balance;
or
2. Fifty Thousand Dollars ($50,000.00).
B. A participant who borrows from his or her account shall repay the
loan within five (5) years, and payments shall be made in substantially
equal payments that include principal and interest and that are paid at
least quarterly. Loan repayments shall not be considered plan
contributions.
C. A loan that is taken for the purpose of purchasing the
participant's principal residence may be paid back over a period of more
than five (5) years.
D. The Board of Trustees shall promulgate such rules as are necessary
to implement the provisions of this section in accordance with applicable
state and federal law."
AMEND TITLE TO CONFORM TO AMENDMENTS
